abstract: The following list has been selected from titles reviewed since the Christmas issue of December 1979. Such a list can only suggest the high points in the main fields of reader interest. Books are arranged alphabetically under subject headings. Quoted comments are from the Book Review.

"Frank Loesser was the only writer I know whose songs got a belly laugh from the audience," mused Abe Burrows, who has written a few madcap ditties himself. "He had to leave a break in the music to allow time for the laughter. But  comedy came easily to him. He respected what was a little harder: it was the romantic stuff he loved best."

abstract: LOS ANGELES, Nov. 28--From Secaucus, N.J., to Wappingers Falls, N.Y., and most cities in between, moviegoers this weekend can get an advance look at four major Christmas movies.
